ENDORSED ORDER: PLAINTIFFS ATTEMPT TO ALLEGE DIVERSITY OF CITIZENSHIP AS THE BASIS FOR THE COURT'S JURISDICTION OVER THIS MATTER |linksToEntryNumber| 1  . HOWEVER, UPON REVIEW OF THE COMPLAINT, THE COURT FINDS THAT PLAINTIFFS HAVE NOT SUFFICIENTLY DEMONSTRATED THAT THE PROPER GROUNDS FOR DIVERSITY JURISDICTION EXIST. AS EXPLAINED IN MOLINOS VALLE DEL CIBAO, C. POR A. V. LAMA, 633 F.3D 1330, 1342 N.12 (11TH CIR. 2011), "CITIZENSHIP, NOT RESIDENCE, IS THE KEY FACT THAT MUST BE ALLEGED... TO ESTABLISH DIVERSITY FOR A NATURAL PERSON." FURTHERMORE, PLAINTIFFS ARE ADVISED THAT TO SUFFICIENTLY ALLEGE CITIZENSHIP OF A CORPORATION, THE PRINCIPAL PLACE OF BUSINESS MUST BE PROVIDED. BECAUSE THE COMPLAINT FAILS TO PROPERLY ALLEGE THE CITIZENSHIP OF EACH PARTY, DIVERSITY HAS NOT BEEN DEFINITIVELY ESTABLISHED. ACCORDINGLY, THE COURT DIRECTS PLAINTIFFS, ON OR BEFORE OCTOBER 20, 2014, TO FILE AN AMENDED COMPLAINT DEMONSTRATING THAT PROPER GROUNDS FOR DIVERSITY JURISDICTION EXIST. FAILURE TO SATISFY THE COURT THAT THE REQUIREMENTS FOR DIVERSITY JURISDICTION EXIST WILL RESULT IN AN ORDER OF DISMISSAL FOR LACK OF JURISDICTION. SIGNED BY JUDGE VIRGINIA M. HERNANDEZ COVINGTON ON 10/14/2014. (KBT) (ENTERED: 10/14/2014)

entrytext: ENDORSED ORDER: PLAINTIFF ATTEMPTS TO ALLEGE DIVERSITY OF CITIZENSHIP AS THE BASIS FOR THE COURT'S JURISDICTION OVER THIS MATTER |linksToEntryNumber| 1  . HOWEVER, UPON REVIEW OF THE COMPLAINT, THE COURT FINDS THAT PLAINTIFF HAS NOT SUFFICIENTLY DEMONSTRATED THAT THE PROPER GROUNDS FOR DIVERSITY JURISDICTION EXIST. DIVERSITY JURISDICTION IN A CASE INVOLVING A LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY IS BASED ON THE CITIZENSHIP OF ALL MEMBERS OF THE LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY. FURTHERMORE, TO PROPERLY ALLEGE THE CITIZENSHIP OF THE DEFENDANT CORPORATION, PLAINTIFF MUST PROVIDE THE CORPORATION'S PRINCIPAL PLACE OF BUSINESS IN ADDITION TO ITS STATE OF INCORPORATION. BECAUSE THE COMPLAINT FAILS TO PROPERLY ALLEGE THE CITIZENSHIP OF EACH PARTY, DIVERSITY HAS NOT BEEN DEFINITIVELY ESTABLISHED. ACCORDINGLY, THE COURT DIRECTS PLAINTIFF, ON OR BEFORE OCTOBER 10, 2014, TO FILE AN AMENDED COMPLAINT DEMONSTRATING THAT PROPER GROUNDS FOR DIVERSITY JURISDICTION EXIST. FAILURE TO SATISFY THE COURT THAT THE REQUIREMENTS FOR DIVERSITY JURISDICTION EXIST WILL RESULT IN AN ORDER OF DISMISSAL FOR LACK OF JURISDICTION. SIGNED BY JUDGE VIRGINIA M. HERNANDEZ COVINGTON ON 10/3/2014. (KBT) (ENTERED: 10/03/2014)

ENDORSED ORDER: PLAINTIFF ATTEMPTS TO ALLEGE DIVERSITY OF CITIZENSHIP AS THE BASIS FOR THE COURT'S JURISDICTION OVER THIS MATTER. |linksToEntryNumber| 1  . HOWEVER, BECAUSE THE COMPLAINT FAILS TO PROPERLY ALLEGE THE CITIZENSHIP OF DEFENDANT, DIVERSITY HAS NOT BEEN DEFINITIVELY ESTABLISHED. IN THE COMPLAINT, PLAINTIFF STATES "DEFENDANT PRINT HARMONY IS A FOREIGN LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY AND IS A CITIZEN OF THE STATES OF NEVADA AND FLORIDA IN THAT IT WAS ORGANIZED IN THE STATE OF NEVADA, AND ITS PRINCIPAL PLACE OF BUSINESS IS IN PINELLAS COUNTY, FLORIDA." DIVERSITY JURISDICTION IN A CASE INVOLVING A LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY IS BASED ON THE CITIZENSHIP OF ALL MEMBERS OF THE LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY. THEREFORE, THE COURT DIRECTS PLAINTIFF TO FILE, ON OR BEFORE OCTOBER 28, 2014, AN AMENDED COMPLAINT DEMONSTRATING DEFENDANT'S CITIZENSHIP SO THAT THE DETERMINATION OF WHETHER DIVERSITY JURISDICTION EXISTS IN THIS MATTER CAN BE ESTABLISHED. FAILURE TO SATISFY THE COURT THAT THE REQUIREMENTS FOR DIVERSITY JURISDICTION EXIST WILL RESULT IN AN ORDER OF DISMISSAL FOR LACK OF JURISDICTION. SIGNED BY JUDGE VIRGINIA M. HERNANDEZ COVINGTON ON 10/21/2014. (KNC) (ENTERED: 10/21/2014)

entrytext: ENDORSED ORDER: ON NOVEMBER 16, 2014, THIS COURT ENTERED AN ORDER DIRECTING PLAINTIFF TO DEMONSTRATE WHY THIS ACTION SHOULD NOT BE DISMISSED AGAINST DEFENDANTS NATIONAL PEN CO. LLC AND NATIONAL PEN HOLDINGS, LLC FOR FAILURE TO PROSECUTE AS A RESULT OF DEFENDANTS FAILURE TO TIMELY FILE A RESPONSE TO PLAINTIFF'S COMPLAINT. 11 . IN RESPONSE TO THE ORDER, PLAINTIFF SUBMITS THAT ITS COUNSEL SPOKE WITH DEFENDANTS' COUNSEL WHO REPRESENTED THAT A MOTION FOR EXTENSION OF TIME TO FILE A RESPONSIVE PLEADING WILL BE FILED NO LATER THAN NOVEMBER 26, 2014. |linksToEntryNumber| 13  . WHILE THE COURT ENCOURAGES COLLEGIALITY IN ACQUIESCING TO EXTENSIONS OF TIME, IT IS ONLY THE COURT THAT CAN GRANT OR DENY SUCH A REQUEST. TO THAT END, THE COURT EXPECTS COUNSEL FOR ALL PARTIES TO FOLLOW THE FEDERAL RULES OF CIVIL PROCEDURE AND THE RULES OF THIS COURT. NONETHELESS, THE COURT FINDS GOOD CAUSE TO GRANT DEFENDANTS NATIONAL PEN CO. LLC AND NATIONAL PEN HOLDINGS, LLC A BRIEF EXTENSION OF TIME IN WHICH TO FILE A RESPONSIVE PLEADING. ACCORDINGLY, DEFENDANTS HAVE UNTIL AND INCLUDING NOVEMBER 26, 2014, TO FILE A RESPONSE TO PLAINTIFF'S COMPLAINT OR A MOTION FOR EXTENSION OF TIME TO DO SO. IF DEFENDANTS FAIL TO TIMELY FILE A RESPONSE OR A MOTION FOR EXTENSION OF TIME, PLAINTIFF HAS UNTIL AND INCLUDING DECEMBER 1, 2014, TO DEMONSTRATE, IN WRITING, WHY THIS ACTION SHOULD NOT BE DISMISSED AGAINST DEFENDANTS NATIONAL PEN CO. LLC AND NATIONAL PEN HOLDINGS, LLC FOR FAILURE TO PROSECUTE PURSUANT TO LOCAL RULE 3.10(A). FAILURE TO DO SO WILL RESULT IN DEFENDANTS BEING DISMISSED FROM THIS ACTION WITHOUT FURTHER NOTICE. SIGNED BY JUDGE VIRGINIA M. HERNANDEZ COVINGTON ON 11/19/2014. (KNC) (ENTERED: 11/19/2014)

entrytext: ENDORSED ORDER: PLAINTIFF ATTEMPTS TO ALLEGE DIVERSITY OF CITIZENSHIP AS THE BASIS FOR THE COURT'S JURISDICTION OVER THIS MATTER |linksToEntryNumber| 1  . HOWEVER, UPON REVIEW OF THE COMPLAINT, THE COURT FINDS THAT PLAINTIFF HAS NOT SUFFICIENTLY DEMONSTRATED THAT THE PROPER GROUNDS FOR DIVERSITY JURISDICTION EXIST. PLAINTIFF IS ADVISED THAT TO SUFFICIENTLY ALLEGE CITIZENSHIP OF A LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY, IT MUST PROVIDE THE CITIZENSHIP OF ALL MEMBERS OF THE LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY. BECAUSE THE COMPLAINT FAILS TO PROPERLY ALLEGE THE CITIZENSHIP OF EACH PARTY, DIVERSITY HAS NOT BEEN DEFINITIVELY ESTABLISHED. ACCORDINGLY, THE COURT DIRECTS PLAINTIFF, ON OR BEFORE NOVEMBER 4, 2014, TO FILE AN AMENDED COMPLAINT DEMONSTRATING THAT PROPER GROUNDS FOR DIVERSITY JURISDICTION EXIST. FAILURE TO SATISFY THE COURT THAT THE REQUIREMENTS FOR DIVERSITY JURISDICTION EXIST WILL RESULT IN AN ORDER OF DISMISSAL FOR LACK OF JURISDICTION. SIGNED BY JUDGE VIRGINIA M.
